<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName LSID="6DBFD633-8975-5406-A923-18D69CC4A4F6" authority="Chang &amp; Pei &amp; Zhu &amp; Ma, 2020" authorityName="Chang &amp; Pei &amp; Zhu &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Lithobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Sinuispineus)" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Sinuispineus">Sinuispineus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="0" pageNumber="43">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName authority="sinuispineus" authorityName="sinuispineus" authorityYear="2020" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Lithobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lithobius (Sinuispineus) sinuispineus" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuispineus" subGenus="Sinuispineus">Lithobius (Sinuispineus) sinuispineus</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName authorityName="sinuispineus" authorityYear="2020" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Lithobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Sinuispineus)" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Sinuispineus">Sinuispineus</taxonomicName>
subgen. nov. differs from the other subgenera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Lithobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lithobius" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Lithobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having curving posterior spurs on dorsal side of the femur of male leg 15; the prefemur and femur and tibia of male leg 15 markedly incrassate; prefemur and femur and tibia of male legs 14 also thicker than legs 1-13. Antennae 20-25 articles, 9-13 ocelli in three irregular rows, posterior two ocelli comparatively large; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tömösváry’s">Toemoesvary's</normalizedToken>
organ larger than the adjacent ocelli; prosternal teeth commonly 2+2, rarely 3+3; posterior angles of all tergites without triangular projections; coxal pore formula 3-6 in one row; tarsal articulation ill-defined on legs 1-13, well-defined on legs 14 and 15; female gonopods with 2+2 moderately small coniform spurs; male gonopods short and small.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">To emphasize the obviously curved posterior spurs on the dorsal side of the femur of the male leg 15.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Fujian and Henan provinces, China.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Chang &amp; Pei &amp; Zhu &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Lithobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lithobius (Sinuispineus)" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Sinuispineus">Lithobius (Sinuispineus)</taxonomicName>
is identified as a member of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Newport &amp; May" authorityYear="1844" family="Lithobiidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="family">Lithobiidae</taxonomicName>
based on the following: forcipular pleurites not meeting ventrally, male gonopods not visible, 9-13 ocelli, antennomeres 20 or thereabouts, posterior angles of all tergites rounded, spiracle lacking on the first leg-bearing segment, spurs lacking on tibia, and at least some legs with regularly disposed distal spurs on various articles. 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Chang &amp; Pei &amp; Zhu &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Lithobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lithobius (Sinuispineus)" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Sinuispineus">Lithobius (Sinuispineus)</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Lithobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lithobius (Monotarsobius)" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Monotarsobius">Lithobius (Monotarsobius)</taxonomicName>
Verhoeff, 1905 but can be readily distinguished by the following characters: posterior spurs on the dorsal side of the femur of legs 15 in males are curved in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chang &amp; Pei &amp; Zhu &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Lithobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Sinuispineus)" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Sinuispineus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Sinuispineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in contrast to straight in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1905" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Monotarsobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Monotarsobius" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Monotarsobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; tarsal articulation ill-defined on legs 1-13 versus very faint or indistinct in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1905" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Monotarsobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Monotarsobius" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Monotarsobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 9-13 ocelli versus ocelli generally few, 1+1-1+11, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1905" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Monotarsobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Monotarsobius" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Monotarsobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
